    "description": "Osaka Organic Chemical Industry Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the production and marketing of organic chemistry industry products, organic reagents, petrochemical products, and special polymers in Japan, China, Asia, Australia, the Americas, and Europe. The company operates in three segments: Chemical Products, Electronic Materials, and Functional Chemicals. It offers chemical products, including biomass acrylates and acrylic monomers for coating raw materials and adhesives; and electronics materials, such as display device and semiconductor materials. The company also provides specialty chemicals comprising cosmetics raw materials, which include cationic, anionic, betaine, nonionic, and acidic thickening polymers; functional materials, such as ink jet and coating materials, as well as esters; and commercialization support for functional monomers and polymers, organic compounds, and medical intermediates. In addition, it offers equipment comprising reaction tanks and distillation columns; and engages in the refining and processing of solvents. The company was founded in 1941 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
